relation: Great for these types of students
There aren't many interesting clubs. They pretty much all focus on academic subjects.
It has a very large multicultural community. Over half the student body is Asian. There's excellent help for those who's first language isn't English.
Very cheap if you want to get pre-reqs and transfer
It has a pretty good cafeteria with a variety of food. There also a peet's coffee stand in front of the library.
I found the classes had a reasonable workload.
